All the faculties in NTU, each student only associated to one Faculty.

The `IReplying` interface defines a contract for replying to comments within a camp.

The `IViewing` interface defines a contract for viewing comments within a camp.

StudentAddSuggestion
The `StudentAddSuggestion` class implements the `IAdding` interface to provide functionality for students to add a suggestion to a camp.

The `StudentDeleteSuggestion` class implements the `IDeleting` interface and is responsible for deleting a suggestion comment in the application.

The `StudentEditEnquiry` class implements the `IEditing` interface and is responsible for editing an existing enquiry comment in the application.
StudentEditSuggestion
The `StudentEditSuggestion` class implements the `IEditing` interface and is responsible for allowing students to edit their own suggestion comments in the application.
StudentEnquiryMenu
The `StudentEnquiryMenu` class represents a menu for students to manage and interact with enquiry comments within the Camp Management System.
StudentMenu
The `StudentMenu` class provides a menu for student users to perform various actions, including joining camps, viewing available and joined camps, withdrawing from registered camps, view and raise enquiries, and accessing the committee menu (if applicable).

The `StudentReplyEnquiry` class implements the `IReplying` interface and allows students to reply to enquiry comments made by other users within a camp.
StudentSuggestionMenu
The `StudentSuggestionMenu` class represents a menu for students to manage and interact with suggestion comments within the Camp Management System.
StudentViewEnquiry
The `StudentViewEnquiry` class implements the `IViewing` interface and allows students to view their own enquiry comments within a camp.
StudentViewSuggestion
The `StudentViewSuggestion` class implements the `IViewing` interface and allows students to view their own suggestion comments within a camp.

The `Suggestion` class represents a suggestion comment made by a camp comittee.

The Suggestion's status can be either PENDING, APPROVED, or REJECTED
User
The `User` abstract class represents a user in the system.
UserMenu
The `UserMenu` abstract class represents a menu for a user with common functionalities.
